  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You had to hitchhike rides with-- we, I think we did catch a train up to the-- at the city near where we had our camp, near the Alba River.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then-- but then it stopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because all the railroad bridges were out, destroyed over the Alba River.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we had to walk over one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was kind of, you know, different.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You had to go past Russian guards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We did have a paper that said that we were survivors.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I don't know if said-- it probably said just Jewish or survivors-- that was written in German and Russian for the benefit of any Russian guides, that we had gotten from one of the, you know, Russian authorities, Russian-German authorities now.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so that that was our best identification.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we went tracking through Germany by foot, railroad, crossing the Alba River bridge, and then going through the rest-- again, on hitchhiking rides, getting an occasional train ride, until we got toward the zone border between Russia, the Russian occupation and US occupation, Bavaria on the other side.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And here, we had to stop.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nobody was, nobody was supposed to go either-- in either direction.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was total-- there had been no agreements yet in how to handle the transit across the different zone borders.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But we didn't want to wait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the very first time we started out, we met up in one of the cities nearby the zone border.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we met up with some-- two German soldiers, ex German soldiers, that also had wanted to go into Bavaria, and a young girl.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
